notes.note: Rec'd estimate for replacement of driver's side axle shaft seal and driver's side axle from Go Auto. Short claim, contract was initiated December 21st 2024. Said axle shaft popped out slightly and fluid is leaking out of the diff. But fluid would leak out if the axle shaft popped out slightly. Going to inquire about how the axle shaft popped out, and why the seal needs to be replaced. Then going to speak with John or Dave to see if they are willing to participate in short claim. M.P.
notes.content: Rec'd estimate for replacement of driver's side axle shaft seal and driver's side axle from Go Auto. Short claim, contract was initiated December 21st 2024. Said axle shaft popped out slightly and fluid is leaking out of the diff. But fluid would leak out if the axle shaft popped out slightly. Going to inquire about how the axle shaft popped out, and why the seal needs to be replaced. Then going to speak with John or Dave to see if they are willing to participate in short claim. M.P.

notes.note: Rec'd picture of shaft popped out. Nathan from Go Auto called to touch base. Said customer drove around Calgary after he purchased the vehicle and saw fluid on the ground. Brought it back for further inspection. Nathan spoke to reps at Dodge, confirmed it is a common failure. Piece inside one of the drive shaft joints fails and allows shaft to pop out due to centrifugal force. No recalls for this concern. Seal damaged as result of shaft being popped out. Proceeding with claim. M.P.

notes.note:
Hey Nathan, thanks for the updated estimate! As previously discussed, thankfully, the replacement of the driver's side cv shaft and axle seal are covered under this customer's warranty contract. Please be advised, the customer is responsible for any diagnostic fees, shop supplies and fluids, as well as a $100 deductible. Additionally, our contracts cover a maximum of $130/h for labour. If you choose to charge the customer the quoted labour rate of $140/h, the customer will be responsible for the difference. The payout is as follows:

Parts-$293.05
Labour-$299.00 (2.3 hours x $130/h)
Deductible-$100.00
Tax-$29.60
Authorization-BJK89IX347

Total = $521.65

Once the repair is complete, please send us a copy of the final invoice for payment.

Best regards, 

Matthew Puls
Claims Adjuster
